data.chText: （英格兰、威尔士和北爱尔兰由议员选举产生的）镇长，市长，郡长
data.enText: (in England, Wales and Northern Ireland) the head of a town, borough or county council, chosen by other members of the council to represent them at official ceremonies, etc.
the head of the government of a town or city, etc., elected by the public

simple_means.memory_skill: may〔= maj〕大，伟大 + or 表名词 → 地位高的人 → 市长

means: (英格兰、威尔士和北爱尔兰由议员选举产生的)镇长

tr: the head of a city government

value.def: The mayor of a town or city is the person who has been elected to represent it for a fixed period of time or, in some places, to run its government.

trans: 市长大人(伦敦市和其他一些英国大城市市长的称号)

partsOfSpeech.dec: maj 大，伟大 + estic 表形容词 → 雄伟的
maj 大，伟大 + or → 较大的；主要的
major 较大的；主要的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 大多数
may〔= maj〕大，伟大 + or 表名词 → 地位高的人 → 市长
